race.description: Newcastle City Kia Super Maiden Handicap
race.comment: APOLLO RIDGE (2) returned with a solid second over 1000m at Kembla then wasn't suited going back in trip on the main course here last time and failed to threaten. Very fit now and nicely placed up to this journey. Watch for a far better performance. CUESTA (9) returned from a five-month spell and recorded her fifth minor placing from six starts when a fast-finishing second over 1000m at Orange. In the money at three of four over today's trip so she is sure to play a prominent role again. BARKING MAD (8) worked home fairly but never looked a chance over 1400m at Warwick Farm recently. Takes on an easier assignment today and can find form at the third run of the preparation. There should be market interest in CHIX (11) on debut from the O'Shea/Charlton stable. Three trials over the last six weeks have all been impressive. Sure to give a good account. ZOYSIA (3) is the interesting runner. Last appeared on debut in September 2024. Now a gelding - betting holds the key.
